description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Do you really want to make a difference? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a senior clinician with expertise in tissue viability and have the leadership skills required to support embedding our citywide wound prevention and management strategy? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Moving forwards with an integrated workforce, an opportunity has arisen for two experienced and innovative tissue viability nurses who are looking for an exciting challenge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This new citywide model of working offers the opportunity to clinically help shape and drive the development of our approach to wound prevention and management across the city. The successful candidates will contribute to key pathways and clinical frameworks and be committed to improving patient care - working within and promoting a case management model. You will provide visible and effective leadership at the point of care. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will have highly developed theoretical and clinical specialist knowledge, with experience in audit, guideline development, implementing quality standards and developing clinical practice. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will require excellent communication skills as well as the ability to work flexibly across the city. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are excited by this potential opportunity then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
